HEADWORD: Brevipennate
<hw>Brev`i*pen"nate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>brevis</ets> short + E. <ets>pennate</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Short-winged; -- applied to birds which can not
fly, owing to their short wings, as the ostrich, cassowary, and
emu.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

